TITLE: Defining Basic Module Structure in Move
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the basic syntax for defining a module in Move, including the module declaration, struct definition, use statement, constant declaration, and a public function.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/move-book/blob/main/reference/src/modules.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
module 0::test;

public struct Example has copy, drop { i: u64 }

use std::debug;

const ONE: u64 = 1;

public fun print(x: u64) {
    let sum = x + ONE;
    let example = Example { i: sum };
    debug::print(&sum)
}
```

