TITLE: Defining a Basic Generic Container in Move
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to define a generic Container struct with a single type parameter T and a creation function that returns a new Container instance. This showcases the basic syntax for defining generic types and functions in Move.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/move-book/blob/main/book/src/move-basics/generics.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
/// A simple container for a single value
struct Container<T> has copy, drop {
    value: T
}

/// Function to create a new container of type T with a value
public fun new<T: copy + drop>(value: T): Container<T> {
    Container<T> { value }
}
```

