TITLE: Demonstrating Basic Ownership in Move
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how variables are owned by their function scopes. Variables 'a' and 'b' are owned by different functions and are dropped when each function ends. The test function shows that these variables are not accessible outside their defining scopes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/move-book/blob/main/book/src/move-basics/ownership-and-scope.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
module book::ownership;

public fun owner() {
    let a = 1; // a is owned by the `owner` function
} // a is dropped here

public fun other() {
    let b = 2; // b is owned by the `other` function
} // b is dropped here

#[test]
fun test_owner() {
    owner();
    other();
    // a & b are not valid here
}
```

