TITLE: Demonstrating Type Reflection in Move
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet illustrates the usage of type reflection in Move using the std::type_name module. It shows how to get type names for various data types, including primitives and custom structs, and how to extract module and address information from type names.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/move-book/blob/main/book/src/move-basics/type-reflection.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
use std::type_name;
use std::string;

struct MyType {}

#[test]
fun test_type_reflection() {
    // Get type names
    let bool_type = type_name::get<bool>();
    let u64_type = type_name::get<u64>();
    let vec_type = type_name::get<vector<u8>>();
    let my_type = type_name::get<MyType>();

    // Convert to string
    let bool_str = type_name::into_string(bool_type);
    assert!(bool_str == string::utf8(b"bool"), 0);

    // Get module name and address
    let (address, module_name) = type_name::get_address_and_module(my_type);
    assert!(module_name == string::utf8(b"type-reflection"), 0);
}
```

