TITLE: Creating a Generic User Type with Metadata in Move
DESCRIPTION: Defines a User struct with generic metadata of type T. This example demonstrates how generics enable a type to have shared behavior while allowing flexible data storage in specific fields.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/move-book/blob/main/book/src/move-basics/generics.md#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
/// A user with metadata of any type
struct User<T: copy + drop + store> has key, copy, drop, store {
    name: vector<u8>,
    age: u8,
    metadata: T
}

/// Create a new user
public fun new_user<T: copy + drop + store>(name: vector<u8>, age: u8, metadata: T): User<T> {
    User {
        name,
        age,
        metadata
