TITLE: Creating and Using Structs in Move
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create struct instances, including named and positional structs. Also shows field name punning for struct creation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/move-book/blob/main/reference/src/structs.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
module a::m;

public struct Foo has drop { x: u64, y: bool }
public struct Baz has drop { foo: Foo }
public struct Positional(u64, bool) has drop;

fun example() {
    let foo = Foo { x: 0, y: false };
    let baz = Baz { foo: foo };
    // Note: positional struct values are created using parentheses and
    // based on position instead of name.
    let pos = Positional(0, false);
    let pos_invalid = Positional(false, 0);
    //                           ^ ERROR! Fields are out of order and the types don't match.
}

let baz = Baz { foo: foo };
// is equivalent to
let baz = Baz { foo };
```

