TITLE: Control Flow Expressions in Move
DESCRIPTION: Shows how control flow constructs in Move (if-else and while loops) are expressions that return values, with examples of assigning the results to variables.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/move-book/blob/main/book/src/move-basics/expression.md#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
fun control_flow() {
    // If-else expression
    let x = if (true) 1 else 2;
    assert!(x == 1, 0);

    // While loop
    let i = 0;
    let sum = 0;
    while (i < 10) {
        sum = sum + i;
        i = i + 1;
    };
    assert!(sum == 45, 0);
}
```

