TITLE: Implementing Vector Iteration Macros in Move
DESCRIPTION: Two macros for iterating over vector elements. 'for_imm' allows immutable iteration with a lambda function applied to each element, while 'for_mut' allows mutable iteration with a function that can modify each element.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/move-book/blob/main/reference/src/functions/macros.md#2025-04-22_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
macro fun for_imm<$T>($v: &vector<$T>, $f: |&$T|) {
    let v = $v;
    let n = v.length();
    let mut i = 0;
    while (i < n) {
        $f(&v[i]);
        i = i + 1;
    }
}

macro fun for_mut<$T>($v: &mut vector<$T>, $f: |&mut $T|) {
    let v = $v;
    let n = v.length();
    let mut i = 0;
    while (i < n) {
        $f(&mut v[i]);
        i = i + 1;
    }
}
```

