TITLE: Using Break in While Loop to Find Position in Vector
DESCRIPTION: This function uses a while loop with a break statement to find the position of a target value in a vector. It returns an Option<u64> containing the index if found, or None if not found.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/move-book/blob/main/reference/src/control-flow/loops.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
fun find_position(values: &vector<u64>, target_value: u64): Option<u64> {
    let size = vector::length(values);
    let mut i = 0;
    let mut found = false;

    while (i < size) {
        if (vector::borrow(values, i) == &target_value) {
            found = true;
            break
        };
        i = i + 1
    };

    if (found) {
        option::some(i)
    } else {
        option::none<u64>()
    }
}
```

