TITLE: Limitations of Guard Expressions in Move
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates limitations of guard expressions in Move pattern matching, particularly regarding mutability. The examples show that variables are only available as immutable references in guards, regardless of the original pattern.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/move-book/blob/main/reference/src/control-flow/pattern-matching.md#2025-04-22_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
fun incr(x: &mut u64) {
    *x = *x + 1;
}

fun match_with_guard_incr(x: u64): u64 {
    match (x) {
        x if ({ incr(&mut x); x == 1 }) => 1,
        // ERROR:    ^^^ invalid borrow of immutable value
        _ => 2,
    }
}

fun match_with_guard_incr2(x: &mut u64): u64 {
    match (x) {
        x if ({ incr(&mut x); x == 1 }) => 1,
        // ERROR:    ^^^ invalid borrow of immutable value
        _ => 2,
    }
}
```

