TITLE: Using Continue in Loop Expression to Sum Even Numbers
DESCRIPTION: This function uses a loop expression with continue to sum only even numbers from a vector. It demonstrates the use of break to exit the loop and continue to skip odd numbers.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/move-book/blob/main/reference/src/control-flow/loops.md#2025-04-22_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
fun sum_even(values: &vector<u64>): u64 {
    let size = vector::length(values);
    let mut i = 0;
    let mut even_sum = 0;

    loop {
        if (i >= size) break;
        let number = *vector::borrow(values, i);
        i = i + 1;
        if (number % 2 == 1) continue;
        even_sum = even_sum + number;
    };
    even_sum
}
```

