TITLE: Implementing Sum with Threshold Using Labeled Loops in Move
DESCRIPTION: Function that sums numbers from nested vectors until reaching a threshold. Uses labeled loops to break out of nested iterations when the threshold would be exceeded.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/move-book/blob/main/reference/src/control-flow/labeled-control-flow.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
fun sum_until_threshold(input: &vector<vector<u64>>, threshold: u64): u64 {
    let mut sum = 0;
    let mut i = 0;
    let input_size = input.length();

    'outer: loop {
        // breaks to outer since it is the closest enclosing loop
        if (i >= input_size) break sum;

        let vec = &input[i];
        let size = vec.length();
        let mut j = 0;

        while (j < size) {
            let v_entry = vec[j];
            if (sum + v_entry < threshold) {
                sum = sum + v_entry;
            } else {
                // the next element we saw would break the threshold,
                // so we return the current sum
                break 'outer sum
            };
            j = j + 1;
        };
        i = i + 1;
    }
}
```

