TITLE: Using Clever Abort Codes in Move
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the #[error] attribute to create custom abort codes with vector<u8> values instead of u64.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/move-book/blob/main/reference/src/abort-and-assert/clever-errors.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
module 0x42::a_module;

#[error]
const EIsThree: vector<u8> = b"The value is three";

// Will abort with `EIsThree` if `x` is 3
public fun double_except_three(x: u64): u64 {
    assert!(x != 3, EIsThree);
    x * x
}

// Will always abort with `EIsThree`
public fun clever_abort() {
    abort EIsThree
}
```

