TITLE: Security Considerations for Random Number Generation - Markdown
DESCRIPTION: Documentation of security considerations and potential issues when implementing random number generation in smart contracts, including predictability concerns and gas optimization strategies.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/move-book/blob/main/book/src/programmability/randomness.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: markdown
CODE:
```
Difficulties:

- If you know the seed, then you can predict the random number.
- Random should not be used in a public function - predictable.
- Random failure is more expensive than a success scenario.
    - one way out is to first calculate randomness and then do a separate expensive operation.
    - they can set a limit to gas for failure scenarios, so the failure never happens.
```

