TITLE: Operators in Move
DESCRIPTION: Shows the use of arithmetic, logical, and bitwise operators in Move, which are expressions that produce values.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/move-book/blob/main/book/src/move-basics/expression.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
fun operators() {
    // Arithmetic operators
    let _ = 1 + 2;
    let _ = 3 - 4;
    let _ = 5 * 6;
    let _ = 7 / 8;
    let _ = 9 % 10;

    // Logical operators
    let _ = true && false;
    let _ = true || false;
    let _ = !true;

    // Comparison operators
    let _ = 1 == 2;
    let _ = 3 != 4;
    let _ = 5 < 6;
    let _ = 7 > 8;
    let _ = 9 <= 10;
    let _ = 11 >= 12;

    // Bitwise operators
    let _ = 1 & 2;
    let _ = 3 | 4;
    let _ = 5 ^ 6;
}
```

