TITLE: Reading Struct Fields in Move
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to read and copy struct field values using dereferencing and the dot operator. The dot operator is shown to be more canonical for reading fields without borrowing.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/move-book/blob/main/reference/src/structs.md#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
let foo = Foo { x: 3, y: true };
let bar = Bar(copy foo);
let x: u64 = *&foo.x;
let y: bool = *&foo.y;
let foo2: Foo = *&bar.0;
```

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
let foo = Foo { x: 3, y: true };
let x = foo.x;  // x == 3
let y = foo.y;  // y == true
```

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
let bar = Bar(Foo { x: 3, y: true });
let x = baz.0.x; // x = 3;
```

