TITLE: Using Borrowing Operator for Built-in Types in Move 2024
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use the new borrowing operator '[]' for accessing elements in built-in types like vectors in Move 2024.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/move-book/blob/main/book/src/guides/2024-migration-guide.md#2025-04-22_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: move
CODE:
```
fun play_vec() {
    let v = vector[1,2,3,4];
    let first = &v[0];         // calls vector::borrow(v, 0)
    let first_mut = &mut v[0]; // calls vector::borrow_mut(v, 0)
    let first_copy = v[0];     // calls *vector::borrow(v, 0)
}
```

